Which of the following `jinja2` expression will solve the variable named `fruit`? Here, the `fruit==banana`.

A. This is {{ fruit }}
B. This is '{{ banana }}'
C. This is '{{ fruit }}'
D. This is {{ banana }}

2. Convert the text in variable `car_name` in the following code using Jinja2 to lowercase.

```
car_name: "Generally, cars are ABUNDUNTLY convenient compared to TTC"
```

A. {{ car_name | lower }}
B. {{ car_name | 'lower' }}
C. {{ "car_name" | 'lower' }}
D. {{ car_name | "lower" }}

3. Convert the text in variable `username` in the following code using Jinja2 to titlecase.

A. {{ username | title }}
B. {{ username | 'Title' }}
C. {{ "username" | 'Title' }}
D. {{ username | "title" }}


In Jinja2, how can you check if a variable is defined?

A. {% check_defined variable %}
B. {% if variable is defined %}
C. {% defined variable %}
D. {{ if defined(variable) }}